    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9417" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Φθί̄η</span></b> , dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Φθί̄ηφι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">Phthia.</span>—(1) the chief
          city of the Myrmidons in Thessaly, on the Spercheius, residence of
          Peleus and Achilles, <i><span class="en">Il. 2.683</span></i>.—(2)
          the region about the city, with Hellas forming the realm of Achilles,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 9.395</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 11.496</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">.—Φθί̄ηνδε</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">to Phthia.</span>
        </div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
